{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":806,"text":"I was excited to be a part\nof the \"Dream\" theme,"},{"time":5010,"text":"and then I found out I'm leading off\nthe \"Nightmare?\" section of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8413,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11972,"text":"And certainly there are things\nabout the climate crisis that qualify."},{"time":16462,"text":"And I have some bad news,"},{"time":18749,"text":"but I have a lot more good news."},{"time":20939,"text":"I'm going to propose three questions"},{"time":24360,"text":"and the answer to the first one"},{"time":27124,"text":"necessarily involves a little bad news."},{"time":29515,"text":"But -- hang on, because the answers\nto the second and third questions"},{"time":34948,"text":"really are very positive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37085,"text":"So the first question is,\n\"Do we really have to change?\""},{"time":42106,"text":"And of course, the Apollo Mission,\namong other things"},{"time":47255,"text":"changed the environmental movement,"},{"time":49600,"text":"really launched the modern\nenvironmental movement."},{"time":52456,"text":"18 months after this Earthrise picture\nwas first seen on earth,"},{"time":56937,"text":"the first Earth Day was organized."},{"time":59561,"text":"And we learned a lot about ourselves"},{"time":62324,"text":"looking back at our planet from space."},{"time":65238,"text":"And one of the things that we learned"},{"time":67055,"text":"confirmed what the scientists\nhave long told us."},{"time":69522,"text":"One of the most essential facts"},{"time":71588,"text":"about the climate crisis\nhas to do with the sky."},{"time":74432,"text":"As this picture illustrates,"},{"time":76232,"text":"the sky is not the vast\nand limitless expanse"},{"time":79297,"text":"that appears when we look up\nfrom the ground."},{"time":82153,"text":"It is a very thin shell of atmosphere"},{"time":86030,"text":"surrounding the planet."},{"time":88449,"text":"That right now is the open sewer\nfor our industrial civilization"},{"time":93669,"text":"as it's currently organized."},{"time":95573,"text":"We are spewing 110 million tons"},{"time":99219,"text":"of heat-trapping global warming pollution\ninto it every 24 hours,"},{"time":104211,"text":"free of charge, go ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106533,"text":"And there are many sources\nof the greenhouse gases,"},{"time":109052,"text":"I'm certainly not going\nto go through them all."},{"time":111316,"text":"I'm going to focus on the main one,"},{"time":113034,"text":"but agriculture is involved,\ndiet is involved, population is involved."},{"time":117446,"text":"Management of forests, transportation,"},{"time":119953,"text":"the oceans, the melting of the permafrost."},{"time":122458,"text":"But I'm going to focus\non the heart of the problem,"},{"time":124888,"text":"which is the fact that we still rely\non dirty, carbon-based fuels"},{"time":129427,"text":"for 85 percent of all the energy\nthat our world burns every year."},{"time":135890,"text":"And you can see from this image\nthat after World War II,"},{"time":139590,"text":"the emission rates\nstarted really accelerating."},{"time":142522,"text":"And the accumulated amount\nof man-made, global warming pollution"},{"time":145875,"text":"that is up in the atmosphere now"},{"time":147425,"text":"traps as much extra heat energy\nas would be released"},{"time":151183,"text":"by 400,000 Hiroshima-class\natomic bombs exploding"},{"time":156656,"text":"every 24 hours, 365 days a year."},{"time":160494,"text":"Fact-checked over and over again,"},{"time":162336,"text":"conservative, it's the truth."},{"time":164557,"text":"Now it's a big planet, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167131,"text":"(Explosion sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169156,"text":"that is a lot of energy,"},{"time":170803,"text":"particularly when you multiply it\n400,000 times per day."},{"time":176881,"text":"And all that extra heat energy"},{"time":178414,"text":"is heating up the atmosphere,\nthe whole earth system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181414,"text":"Let's look at the atmosphere."},{"time":183388,"text":"This is a depiction"},{"time":184702,"text":"of what we used to think of as\nthe normal distribution of temperatures."},{"time":190191,"text":"The white represents\nnormal temperature days;"},{"time":193302,"text":"1951-1980 are arbitrarily chosen."},{"time":196367,"text":"The blue are cooler than average days,"},{"time":198271,"text":"the red are warmer than average days."},{"time":200546,"text":"But the entire curve has moved\nto the right in the 1980s."},{"time":204728,"text":"And you'll see\nin the lower right-hand corner"},{"time":206903,"text":"the appearance of statistically\nsignificant numbers"},{"time":209370,"text":"of extremely hot days."},{"time":210972,"text":"In the 90s, the curve shifted further."},{"time":212969,"text":"And in the last 10 years,\nyou see the extremely hot days"},{"time":216684,"text":"are now more numerous\nthan the cooler than average days."},{"time":220375,"text":"In fact, they are 150 times more common\non the surface of the earth"},{"time":225855,"text":"than they were just 30 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229713,"text":"So we're having\nrecord-breaking temperatures."},{"time":232807,"text":"Fourteen of the 15 of the hottest years\never measured with instruments"},{"time":236154,"text":"have been in this young century."},{"time":237717,"text":"The hottest of all was last year."},{"time":240274,"text":"Last month was the 371st month in a row"},{"time":243795,"text":"warmer than the 20th-century average."},{"time":245986,"text":"And for the first time,\nnot only the warmest January,"},{"time":249190,"text":"but for the first time, it was more\nthan two degrees Fahrenheit warmer"},{"time":254275,"text":"than the average."},{"time":256381,"text":"These higher temperatures\nare having an effect on animals,"},{"time":260309,"text":"plants, people, ecosystems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263396,"text":"But on a global basis, 93 percent\nof all the extra heat energy"},{"time":268342,"text":"is trapped in the oceans."},{"time":270116,"text":"And the scientists can measure\nthe heat buildup"},{"time":272347,"text":"much more precisely now"},{"time":273640,"text":"at all depths: deep, mid-ocean,"},{"time":275895,"text":"the first few hundred meters."},{"time":277959,"text":"And this, too, is accelerating."},{"time":280578,"text":"It goes back more than a century."},{"time":282231,"text":"And more than half of the increase\nhas been in the last 19 years."},{"time":286642,"text":"This has consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287989,"text":"The first order of consequence:"},{"time":289556,"text":"the ocean-based storms get stronger."},{"time":291534,"text":"Super Typhoon Haiyan\nwent over areas of the Pacific"},{"time":294010,"text":"five and a half degrees Fahrenheit\nwarmer than normal"},{"time":297353,"text":"before it slammed into Tacloban,"},{"time":299870,"text":"as the most destructive storm\never to make landfall."},{"time":303917,"text":"Pope Francis, who has made\nsuch a difference to this whole issue,"},{"time":308561,"text":"visited Tacloban right after that."},{"time":310890,"text":"Superstorm Sandy went over\nareas of the Atlantic"},{"time":313493,"text":"nine degrees warmer than normal"},{"time":315875,"text":"before slamming into\nNew York and New Jersey."},{"time":319954,"text":"The second order of consequences\nare affecting all of us right now."},{"time":323146,"text":"The warmer oceans are evaporating\nmuch more water vapor into the skies."},{"time":328901,"text":"Average humidity worldwide\nhas gone up four percent."},{"time":332755,"text":"And it creates these atmospheric rivers."},{"time":335472,"text":"The Brazilian scientists\ncall them \"flying rivers.\""},{"time":338514,"text":"And they funnel all of that\nextra water vapor over the land"},{"time":343281,"text":"where storm conditions trigger\nthese massive record-breaking downpours."},{"time":348567,"text":"This is from Montana."},{"time":351331,"text":"Take a look at this storm last August."},{"time":353678,"text":"As it moves over Tucson, Arizona."},{"time":356021,"text":"It literally splashes off the city."},{"time":359829,"text":"These downpours are really unusual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363056,"text":"Last July in Houston, Texas,"},{"time":366231,"text":"it rained for two days,\n162 billion gallons."},{"time":369209,"text":"That represents more than two days\nof the full flow of Niagara Falls"},{"time":373296,"text":"in the middle of the city,"},{"time":374565,"text":"which was, of course, paralyzed."},{"time":376492,"text":"These record downpours are creating\nhistoric floods and mudslides."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380864,"text":"This one is from Chile last year."},{"time":385175,"text":"And you'll see that warehouse going by."},{"time":388342,"text":"There are oil tankers cars going by."},{"time":390970,"text":"This is from Spain last September,"},{"time":392930,"text":"you could call this the running\nof the cars and trucks, I guess."},{"time":397865,"text":"Every night on the TV news now\nis like a nature hike"},{"time":400717,"text":"through the Book of Revelation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402575,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404990,"text":"I mean, really."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407056,"text":"The insurance industry\nhas certainly noticed,"},{"time":409726,"text":"the losses have been mounting up."},{"time":411970,"text":"They're not under any illusions\nabout what's happening."},{"time":415972,"text":"And the causality requires\na moment of discussion."},{"time":421266,"text":"We're used to thinking of linear cause\nand linear effect --"},{"time":424604,"text":"one cause, one effect."},{"time":425779,"text":"This is systemic causation."},{"time":429009,"text":"As the great Kevin Trenberth says,"},{"time":431272,"text":"\"All storms are different now."},{"time":432756,"text":"There's so much extra energy\nin the atmosphere,"},{"time":435019,"text":"there's so much extra water vapor."},{"time":436708,"text":"Every storm is different now.\""},{"time":439725,"text":"So, the same extra heat pulls\nthe soil moisture out of the ground"},{"time":444090,"text":"and causes these deeper, longer,\nmore pervasive droughts"},{"time":448524,"text":"and many of them are underway right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450638,"text":"It dries out the vegetation"},{"time":452176,"text":"and causes more fires\nin the western part of North America."},{"time":455862,"text":"There's certainly been evidence\nof that, a lot of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459345,"text":"More lightning,"},{"time":460520,"text":"as the heat energy builds up,\nthere's a considerable amount"},{"time":463326,"text":"of additional lightning also."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466710,"text":"These climate-related disasters also have\ngeopolitical consequences"},{"time":473602,"text":"and create instability."},{"time":475436,"text":"The climate-related historic drought\nthat started in Syria in 2006"},{"time":480736,"text":"destroyed 60 percent\nof the farms in Syria,"},{"time":483712,"text":"killed 80 percent of the livestock,"},{"time":486077,"text":"and drove 1.5 million climate refugees\ninto the cities of Syria,"},{"time":490320,"text":"where they collided with another\n1.5 million refugees"},{"time":493573,"text":"from the Iraq War."},{"time":495985,"text":"And along with other factors,\nthat opened the gates of Hell"},{"time":500234,"text":"that people are trying to close now."},{"time":503438,"text":"The US Defense Department has long warned"},{"time":505876,"text":"of consequences from the climate crisis,"},{"time":508198,"text":"including refugees,\nfood and water shortages"},{"time":512749,"text":"and pandemic disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514653,"text":"Right now we're seeing microbial diseases\nfrom the tropics spread"},{"time":519406,"text":"to the higher latitudes;"},{"time":520690,"text":"the transportation revolution has had\na lot to do with this."},{"time":524332,"text":"But the changing conditions\nchange the latitudes and the areas"},{"time":528021,"text":"where these microbial diseases\ncan become endemic"},{"time":531878,"text":"and change the range of the vectors,\nlike mosquitoes and ticks that carry them."},{"time":536641,"text":"The Zika epidemic now --"},{"time":540133,"text":"we're better positioned in North America"},{"time":542074,"text":"because it's still a little too cool\nand we have a better public health system."},{"time":546788,"text":"But when women in some regions\nof South and Central America"},{"time":551112,"text":"are advised not to get pregnant\nfor two years --"},{"time":553847,"text":"that's something new,\nthat ought to get our attention."},{"time":557961,"text":"The Lancet, one of the two greatest\nmedical journals in the world,"},{"time":561133,"text":"last summer labeled this\na medical emergency now."},{"time":565387,"text":"And there are many factors because of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568073,"text":"This is also connected\nto the extinction crisis."},{"time":570894,"text":"We're in danger of losing 50 percent\nof all the living species on earth"},{"time":574465,"text":"by the end of this century."},{"time":575812,"text":"And already, land-based plants and animals"},{"time":578598,"text":"are now moving towards the poles"},{"time":580270,"text":"at an average rate of 15 feet per day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584661,"text":"Speaking of the North Pole,"},{"time":585995,"text":"last December 29, the same storm\nthat caused historic flooding"},{"time":591289,"text":"in the American Midwest,"},{"time":592962,"text":"raised temperatures at the North Pole"},{"time":595169,"text":"50 degrees Fahrenheit warmer than normal,"},{"time":597823,"text":"causing the thawing of the North Pole"},{"time":600285,"text":"in the middle of the long,\ndark, winter, polar night."},{"time":604921,"text":"And when the land-based ice\nof the Arctic melts,"},{"time":608527,"text":"it raises sea level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610269,"text":"Paul Nicklen's beautiful photograph\nfrom Svalbard illustrates this."},{"time":614474,"text":"It's more dangerous coming off Greenland"},{"time":616458,"text":"and particularly, Antarctica."},{"time":618488,"text":"The 10 largest risk cities\nfor sea-level rise by population"},{"time":623202,"text":"are mostly in South and Southeast Asia."},{"time":625965,"text":"When you measure it by assets at risk,\nnumber one is Miami:"},{"time":630098,"text":"three and a half trillion dollars at risk."},{"time":632745,"text":"Number three: New York and Newark."},{"time":634440,"text":"I was in Miami last fall\nduring the supermoon,"},{"time":637760,"text":"one of the highest high-tide days."},{"time":640895,"text":"And there were fish from the ocean\nswimming in some of the streets"},{"time":644051,"text":"of Miami Beach and Fort Lauderdale"},{"time":646226,"text":"and Del Rey."},{"time":647424,"text":"And this happens regularly\nduring the highest-tide tides now."},{"time":650422,"text":"Not with rain -- they call it\n\"sunny-day flooding.\""},{"time":653061,"text":"It comes up through the storm sewers."},{"time":657636,"text":"And the Mayor of Miami\nspeaks for many when he says"},{"time":662024,"text":"it is long past time this can be viewed\nthrough a partisan lens."},{"time":666271,"text":"This is a crisis\nthat's getting worse day by day."},{"time":669431,"text":"We have to move beyond partisanship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671776,"text":"And I want to take a moment\nto honor these House Republicans --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":675062,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676140,"text":"who had the courage last fall"},{"time":678997,"text":"to step out and take a political risk,"},{"time":683455,"text":"by telling the truth\nabout the climate crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686218,"text":"So the cost of the climate\ncrisis is mounting up,"},{"time":689399,"text":"there are many of these aspects\nI haven't even mentioned."},{"time":693091,"text":"It's an enormous burden."},{"time":695088,"text":"I'll mention just one more,"},{"time":696676,"text":"because the World Economic Forum\nlast month in Davos,"},{"time":701427,"text":"after their annual survey\nof 750 economists,"},{"time":704468,"text":"said the climate crisis is now\nthe number one risk"},{"time":707352,"text":"to the global economy."},{"time":709205,"text":"So you get central bankers"},{"time":710547,"text":"like Mark Carney, the head\nof the UK Central Bank,"},{"time":713341,"text":"saying the vast majority\nof the carbon reserves are unburnable."},{"time":717401,"text":"Subprime carbon."},{"time":719171,"text":"I'm not going to remind you what happened\nwith subprime mortgages,"},{"time":722486,"text":"but it's the same thing."},{"time":724112,"text":"If you look at all of the carbon fuels\nthat were burned"},{"time":726851,"text":"since the beginning\nof the industrial revolution,"},{"time":729545,"text":"this is the quantity burned\nin the last 16 years."},{"time":733085,"text":"Here are all the ones that are proven\nand left on the books,"},{"time":736688,"text":"28 trillion dollars."},{"time":738500,"text":"The International Energy Agency\nsays only this amount can be burned."},{"time":742733,"text":"So the rest, 22 trillion dollars --"},{"time":745646,"text":"unburnable."},{"time":747303,"text":"Risk to the global economy."},{"time":749560,"text":"That's why divestment movement\nmakes practical sense"},{"time":752621,"text":"and is not just a moral imperative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755225,"text":"So the answer to the first question,\n\"Must we change?\""},{"time":759419,"text":"is yes, we have to change."},{"time":761367,"text":"Second question, \"Can we change?\""},{"time":763143,"text":"This is the exciting news!"},{"time":765488,"text":"The best projections\nin the world 16 years ago"},{"time":769017,"text":"were that by 2010, the world\nwould be able to install"},{"time":773072,"text":"30 gigawatts of wind capacity."},{"time":775263,"text":"We beat that mark\nby 14 and a half times over."},{"time":780278,"text":"We see an exponential curve\nfor wind installations now."},{"time":784086,"text":"We see the cost coming down dramatically."},{"time":787685,"text":"Some countries -- take Germany,\nan industrial powerhouse"},{"time":790959,"text":"with a climate not that different\nfrom Vancouver's, by the way --"},{"time":794351,"text":"one day last December,"},{"time":796010,"text":"got 81 percent of all its energy\nfrom renewable resources,"},{"time":799472,"text":"mainly solar and wind."},{"time":801129,"text":"A lot of countries are getting\nmore than half on an average basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804454,"text":"More good news:"},{"time":805636,"text":"energy storage,\nfrom batteries particularly,"},{"time":808683,"text":"is now beginning to take off"},{"time":810301,"text":"because the cost has been\ncoming down very dramatically"},{"time":814118,"text":"to solve the intermittency problem."},{"time":815915,"text":"With solar, the news is even\nmore exciting!"},{"time":818450,"text":"The best projections 14 years ago\nwere that we would install"},{"time":821823,"text":"one gigawatt per year by 2010."},{"time":824394,"text":"When 2010 came around,\nwe beat that mark by 17 times over."},{"time":829038,"text":"Last year, we beat it by 58 times over."},{"time":832647,"text":"This year, we're on track\nto beat it 68 times over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835911,"text":"We're going to win this."},{"time":837125,"text":"We are going to prevail."},{"time":838883,"text":"The exponential curve on solar\nis even steeper and more dramatic."},{"time":842990,"text":"When I came to this stage 10 years ago,"},{"time":844943,"text":"this is where it was."},{"time":846894,"text":"We have seen a revolutionary breakthrough"},{"time":850472,"text":"in the emergence\nof these exponential curves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853685,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":856933,"text":"And the cost has come down\n10 percent per year"},{"time":860454,"text":"for 30 years."},{"time":861777,"text":"And it's continuing to come down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864099,"text":"Now, the business community\nhas certainly noticed this,"},{"time":866769,"text":"because it's crossing\nthe grid parity point."},{"time":869602,"text":"Cheaper solar penetration rates\nare beginning to rise."},{"time":872878,"text":"Grid parity is understood\nas that line, that threshold,"},{"time":876418,"text":"below which renewable electricity\nis cheaper than electricity"},{"time":880316,"text":"from burning fossil fuels."},{"time":882558,"text":"That threshold is a little bit\nlike the difference"},{"time":885275,"text":"between 32 degrees Fahrenheit\nand 33 degrees Fahrenheit,"},{"time":889409,"text":"or zero and one Celsius."},{"time":891019,"text":"It's a difference of more than one degree,"},{"time":893067,"text":"it's the difference between ice and water."},{"time":895792,"text":"And it's the difference between markets\nthat are frozen up,"},{"time":899760,"text":"and liquid flows of capital\ninto new opportunities for investment."},{"time":904316,"text":"This is the biggest\nnew business opportunity"},{"time":907945,"text":"in the history of the world,"},{"time":909501,"text":"and two-thirds of it\nis in the private sector."},{"time":912673,"text":"We are seeing an explosion\nof new investment."},{"time":916133,"text":"Starting in 2010, investments globally\nin renewable electricity generation"},{"time":921725,"text":"surpassed fossils."},{"time":923282,"text":"The gap has been growing ever since."},{"time":925722,"text":"The projections for the future\nare even more dramatic,"},{"time":928694,"text":"even though fossil energy\nis now still subsidized"},{"time":932317,"text":"at a rate 40 times larger than renewables."},{"time":935568,"text":"And by the way, if you add\nthe projections for nuclear on here,"},{"time":939682,"text":"particularly if you assume\nthat the work many are doing"},{"time":942327,"text":"to try to break through to safer\nand more acceptable,"},{"time":945065,"text":"more affordable forms of nuclear,"},{"time":946928,"text":"this could change even more dramatically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949934,"text":"So is there any precedent\nfor such a rapid adoption"},{"time":952914,"text":"of a new technology?"},{"time":954667,"text":"Well, there are many,\nbut let's look at cell phones."},{"time":957151,"text":"In 1980, AT&amp;T, then Ma Bell,"},{"time":960548,"text":"commissioned McKinsey to do\na global market survey"},{"time":962965,"text":"of those clunky new mobile phones\nthat appeared then."},{"time":966605,"text":"\"How many can we sell\nby the year 2000?\" they asked."},{"time":969792,"text":"McKinsey came back and said, \"900,000.\""},{"time":972384,"text":"And sure enough,\nwhen the year 2000 arrived,"},{"time":974480,"text":"they did sell 900,000 --\nin the first three days."},{"time":977082,"text":"And for the balance of the year,\nthey sold 120 times more."},{"time":981018,"text":"And now there are more cell connections\nthan there are people in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985418,"text":"So, why were they not only wrong,\nbut way wrong?"},{"time":989911,"text":"I've asked that question myself, \"Why?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":992335,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":993362,"text":"And I think the answer is in three parts."},{"time":996122,"text":"First, the cost came down much faster\nthan anybody expected,"},{"time":999535,"text":"even as the quality went up."},{"time":1002066,"text":"And low-income countries, places\nthat did not have a landline grid --"},{"time":1006362,"text":"they leap-frogged to the new technology."},{"time":1008614,"text":"The big expansion has been\nin the developing counties."},{"time":1011702,"text":"So what about the electricity grids\nin the developing world?"},{"time":1015474,"text":"Well, not so hot."},{"time":1017228,"text":"And in many areas, they don't exist."},{"time":1019550,"text":"There are more people\nwithout any electricity at all in India"},{"time":1022720,"text":"than the entire population\nof the United States of America."},{"time":1025866,"text":"So now we're getting this:"},{"time":1027394,"text":"solar panels on grass huts"},{"time":1029256,"text":"and new business models\nthat make it affordable."},{"time":1032218,"text":"Muhammad Yunus financed\nthis one in Bangladesh with micro-credit."},{"time":1037127,"text":"This is a village market."},{"time":1038859,"text":"Bangladesh is now the fastest-deploying\ncountry in the world:"},{"time":1041773,"text":"two systems per minute\non average, night and day."},{"time":1044209,"text":"And we have all we need:"},{"time":1045422,"text":"enough energy from the Sun\ncomes to the earth"},{"time":1047738,"text":"every hour to supply the full world's\nenergy needs for an entire year."},{"time":1053125,"text":"It's actually a little bit\nless than an hour."},{"time":1055322,"text":"So the answer to the second question,\n\"Can we change?\""},{"time":1058678,"text":"is clearly \"Yes.\""},{"time":1060625,"text":"And it's an ever-firmer \"yes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063421,"text":"Last question, \"Will we change?\""},{"time":1066053,"text":"Paris really was a breakthrough,"},{"time":1068069,"text":"some of the provisions are binding"},{"time":1069756,"text":"and the regular reviews will matter a lot."},{"time":1071818,"text":"But nations aren't waiting,\nthey're going ahead."},{"time":1074093,"text":"China has already announced\nthat starting next year,"},{"time":1076632,"text":"they're adopting a nationwide\ncap and trade system."},{"time":1079639,"text":"They will likely link up\nwith the European Union."},{"time":1082806,"text":"The United States\nhas already been changing."},{"time":1085322,"text":"All of these coal plants were proposed"},{"time":1087396,"text":"in the next 10 years and canceled."},{"time":1089950,"text":"All of these existing\ncoal plants were retired."},{"time":1092893,"text":"All of these coal plants have had\ntheir retirement announced."},{"time":1095934,"text":"All of them -- canceled."},{"time":1098286,"text":"We are moving forward."},{"time":1099800,"text":"Last year -- if you look at\nall of the investment"},{"time":1102292,"text":"in new electricity generation\nin the United States,"},{"time":1105259,"text":"almost three-quarters\nwas from renewable energy,"},{"time":1107949,"text":"mostly wind and solar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1110485,"text":"We are solving this crisis."},{"time":1113656,"text":"The only question is:\nhow long will it take to get there?"},{"time":1118579,"text":"So, it matters that a lot\nof people are organizing"},{"time":1123220,"text":"to insist on this change."},{"time":1125382,"text":"Almost 400,000 people\nmarched in New York City"},{"time":1129190,"text":"before the UN special session on this."},{"time":1132061,"text":"Many thousands, tens of thousands,"},{"time":1134089,"text":"marched in cities around the world."},{"time":1136986,"text":"And so, I am extremely optimistic."},{"time":1141153,"text":"As I said before,\nwe are going to win this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143732,"text":"I'll finish with this story."},{"time":1146218,"text":"When I was 13 years old,"},{"time":1148834,"text":"I heard that proposal by President Kennedy"},{"time":1152289,"text":"to land a person on the Moon\nand bring him back safely"},{"time":1154864,"text":"in 10 years."},{"time":1156053,"text":"And I heard adults\nof that day and time say,"},{"time":1159061,"text":"\"That's reckless, expensive,\nmay well fail.\""},{"time":1162602,"text":"But eight years and two months later,"},{"time":1164803,"text":"in the moment that Neil Armstrong\nset foot on the Moon,"},{"time":1168089,"text":"there was great cheer that went up\nin NASA's mission control in Houston."},{"time":1172703,"text":"Here's a little-known fact about that:"},{"time":1175187,"text":"the average age of the systems engineers,"},{"time":1177416,"text":"the controllers in the room\nthat day, was 26,"},{"time":1180616,"text":"which means, among other things,"},{"time":1182199,"text":"their age, when they heard\nthat challenge, was 18."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1185473,"text":"We now have a moral challenge"},{"time":1188699,"text":"that is in the tradition of others\nthat we have faced."},{"time":1192253,"text":"One of the greatest poets\nof the last century in the US,"},{"time":1195931,"text":"Wallace Stevens,"},{"time":1197304,"text":"wrote a line that has stayed with me:"},{"time":1199146,"text":"\"After the final 'no,'\nthere comes a 'yes,'"},{"time":1201653,"text":"and on that 'yes',\nthe future world depends.\""},{"time":1204658,"text":"When the abolitionists\nstarted their movement,"},{"time":1206967,"text":"they met with no after no after no."},{"time":1209198,"text":"And then came a yes."},{"time":1210498,"text":"The Women's Suffrage\nand Women's Rights Movement"},{"time":1212911,"text":"met endless no's, until finally,\nthere was a yes."},{"time":1216530,"text":"The Civil Rights Movement,\nthe movement against apartheid,"},{"time":1219325,"text":"and more recently, the movement\nfor gay and lesbian rights"},{"time":1222940,"text":"here in the United States and elsewhere."},{"time":1225369,"text":"After the final \"no\" comes a \"yes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1227569,"text":"When any great moral challenge\nis ultimately resolved"},{"time":1232726,"text":"into a binary choice\nbetween what is right and what is wrong,"},{"time":1236605,"text":"the outcome is fore-ordained\nbecause of who we are as human beings."},{"time":1240758,"text":"Ninety-nine percent of us,\nthat is where we are now"},{"time":1244635,"text":"and it is why we're going to win this."},{"time":1247151,"text":"We have everything we need."},{"time":1249113,"text":"Some still doubt that we have\nthe will to act,"},{"time":1252552,"text":"but I say the will to act is itself\na renewable resource."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1257266,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1258497,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1295319,"text":"Chris Anderson: You've got this incredible\ncombination of skills."},{"time":1298526,"text":"You've got this scientist mind\nthat can understand"},{"time":1301511,"text":"the full range of issues,"},{"time":1303836,"text":"and the ability to turn it\ninto the most vivid language."},{"time":1307512,"text":"No one else can do that,\nthat's why you led this thing."},{"time":1310419,"text":"It was amazing to see it 10 years ago,\nit was amazing to see it now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313854,"text":"Al Gore: Well, you're nice\nto say that, Chris."},{"time":1316053,"text":"But honestly, I have a lot\nof really good friends"},{"time":1319238,"text":"in the scientific community\nwho are incredibly patient"},{"time":1322981,"text":"and who will sit there\nand explain this stuff to me"},{"time":1325776,"text":"over and over and over again"},{"time":1327134,"text":"until I can get it\ninto simple enough language"},{"time":1330754,"text":"that I can understand it."},{"time":1331990,"text":"And that's the key to trying\nto communicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1335497,"text":"CA: So, your talk. First part: terrifying,"},{"time":1339206,"text":"second part: incredibly hopeful."},{"time":1341810,"text":"How do we know that all those graphs,\nall that progress, is enough"},{"time":1347135,"text":"to solve what you showed\nin the first part?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1349887,"text":"AG: I think that the crossing --"},{"time":1353439,"text":"you know, I've only been\nin the business world for 15 years."},{"time":1356476,"text":"But one of the things I've learned\nis that apparently it matters"},{"time":1359778,"text":"if a new product or service\nis more expensive"},{"time":1362966,"text":"than the incumbent, or cheaper than."},{"time":1365144,"text":"Turns out, it makes a difference\nif it's cheaper than."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1367723,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1368842,"text":"And when it crosses that line,"},{"time":1371560,"text":"then a lot of things really change."},{"time":1373480,"text":"We are regularly surprised\nby these developments."},{"time":1376449,"text":"The late Rudi Dornbusch,\nthe great economist said,"},{"time":1379020,"text":"\"Things take longer to happen\nthen you think they will,"},{"time":1381840,"text":"and then they happen much faster\nthan you thought they could.\""},{"time":1384822,"text":"I really think that's where we are."},{"time":1386544,"text":"Some people are using the phrase\n\"The Solar Singularity\" now,"},{"time":1390245,"text":"meaning when it gets\nbelow the grid parity,"},{"time":1393562,"text":"unsubsidized in most places,"},{"time":1395634,"text":"then it's the default choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1397300,"text":"Now, in one of the presentations\nyesterday, the jitney thing,"},{"time":1403314,"text":"there is an effort to use\nregulations to slow this down."},{"time":1408445,"text":"And I just don't think it's going to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1412608,"text":"There's a woman in Atlanta, Debbie Dooley,"},{"time":1415028,"text":"who's the Chairman\nof the Atlanta Tea Party."},{"time":1417133,"text":"They enlisted her\nin this effort to put a tax"},{"time":1419334,"text":"on solar panels and regulations."},{"time":1421481,"text":"And she had just put\nsolar panels on her roof"},{"time":1423624,"text":"and she didn't understand the request."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1425514,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1427303,"text":"And so she went and formed\nan alliance with the Sierra Club"},{"time":1430805,"text":"and they formed a new organization\ncalled the Green Tea Party."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1434882,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1435908,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1436933,"text":"And they defeated the proposal."},{"time":1438445,"text":"So, finally, the answer\nto your question is,"},{"time":1441695,"text":"this sounds a little corny\nand maybe it's a cliché,"},{"time":1444752,"text":"but 10 years ago -- and Christiana\nreferred to this --"},{"time":1448292,"text":"there are people in this audience\nwho played an incredibly significant role"},{"time":1454223,"text":"in generating those exponential curves."},{"time":1457048,"text":"And it didn't work out economically\nfor some of them,"},{"time":1459596,"text":"but it kick-started\nthis global revolution."},{"time":1462674,"text":"And what people in this audience do now"},{"time":1466477,"text":"with the knowledge\nthat we are going to win this."},{"time":1469006,"text":"But it matters a lot how fast we win it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1473260,"text":"CA: Al Gore, that was incredibly powerful."},{"time":1475641,"text":"If this turns out to be the year,"},{"time":1477340,"text":"that the partisan thing changes,"},{"time":1480192,"text":"as you said, it's no longer\na partisan issue,"},{"time":1483594,"text":"but you bring along people\nfrom the other side together,"},{"time":1487784,"text":"backed by science, backed by these kinds\nof investment opportunities,"},{"time":1491093,"text":"backed by reason that you win the day --"},{"time":1493225,"text":"boy, that's really exciting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1495608,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1496800,"text":"AG: Thank you so much\nfor bringing me back to TED."},{"time":1499331,"text":"Thank you!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1500506,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}